Please provide your input in regards to the safety and health of your child, as we consider alternative formats for learning for the upcoming school year.

This survey will need to be completed separately for each school-aged child in your household.

Your feedback based on your experiences is important and valued. Please submit your feedback by Thursday, June 25, 2020, using the link below.

Thank you.

Recruitment for the next cohort of NetSERVE Teacher Residents is underway!

Teacher Residents benefit from a 50% tuition reduction, 30 hours streamlined pathway to earning a Master of Arts in Teaching and licensure credentials to teach in South Carolina schools; a year-long $20,000 stipend supported internship; and a job placement guarantee in one of three high-needs, rural partner school districts.

Information sessions to give more details and answer questions about the NetSERVE Teacher Residency program and cohort application process have been scheduled. Visit www.wunetserve.com to get registered to attend the next online session scheduled for Thursday, April 30th at 7 pm or Tuesday, May 5th at 7pm. Winthrop University

post_text:
FCSD has partnered with Winthrop University to provide a unique teacher preparation opportunity for individuals interested in making a difference in South Carolina rural communities. The NetSERVE Teacher Residency program is currently recruiting for the second cohort of teacher residents. An online information session is scheduled for Thursday, April 23rd at 3:00 pm. To learn more, visit www.wunetserve.com

The Teacher Residency program is a graduate program (earn a Master of Arts in Teaching) and the path to teacher certification for people with non-education undergraduate degrees who are interested in becoming teachers in Fairfield as well as Chester and Chesterfield school districts. The program offers potential candidates a year-long residency, $20,000 living expense stipend, and a teaching job in the participating district with successful completion of the program. Winthrop University

post_text:
By order of the Governor of South Carolina, school is canceled for Fairfield County School District students starting March 16, 2020, through March 31, 2020. With the closure of schools, all student activities, including athletics, are canceled from March 16 - March 31. Staff should report at the normal time.

While school is closed, free grab and go breakfasts and lunches for students up to age 18 will be made available. The meals on tomorrow will be distributed through pick-up lines outside of school at all locations. Breakfasts will be distributed 8-9 a.m. and lunches 11 a.m.-1 p.m. In the effort to support social-distancing practices, the meals cannot be consumed on-site.

Learning packets have been developed by grade level for all students. Learning packets can be picked up on Tuesday, March 17th from 7 a.m. - 4 p.m. at the school your son/daughter attends.

Parents should also contact the school nurse directly to pick up any prescribed medications.

Dr. J.R. Green
Superintendent of Schools

Participants may register individually or as a team. Questions may be addressed to Claudia Avery, President at 803.319.4883 or cavery@fairfield1.org.

Thank you for supporting the Winnsboro Rotary Club.

post_text:
Fairfield County School District is looking forward to a productive day where we will continue to focus on teaching and learning. Over the past 12 hours, there have been rumors of threats of violence toward multiple schools throughout South Carolina, to include Fairfield Central High School. The Fairfield County Sheriff’s Office has been investigating these rumors since they have surfaced and have found no substantiated or credible threats thus far.

In the interest of alleviating any concerns that students, staff, and parents may have, the Fairfield County Sheriff’s Office is providing an increased law enforcement presence in our schools throughout the day.

Claudia Avery, PhD
Deputy Superintendent of Academics
Fairfield County School District
